properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 8:14AM MST until February 8 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...TRAVEL IMPACTS WILL CONTINUE ALONG AND WEST OF THE LARAMIE RANGE
THROUGH THIS AFTERNOON...

* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of
up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 55 mph.

* WHERE...South Laramie Range including Vedauwoo and the
Interstate 80 Summit.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM MST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON... ...BLIZZARD WARNING IS CANCELLED
